# Performance

## Mandatory Standards (MUST)
- Do not store large objects or arrays in component state unnecessarily
- Use memoization (React.memo, useMemo, useCallback) for heavy computations and renders
- Avoid unnecessary re-renders due to incorrect effect dependencies
- Optimize resource loading (lazy loading, preloading)
- Minimize the number of DOM repaints

## Recommendations (SHOULD)
- Break down large components into smaller ones
- Use lazy loading for heavy modules and components
- Apply virtualization for long lists
- Use web workers for heavy computations
- Optimize bundle size (tree-shaking, code-splitting)

## Examples
```tsx
// ✅ Correct
const memoizedValue = useMemo(() => computeHeavy(data), [data]);

const HeavyComponent = React.lazy(() => import('./HeavyComponent'));

function MyComponent() {
  return (
    <React.Suspense fallback={<Spinner />}>
      <HeavyComponent />
    </React.Suspense>
  );
}

// ❌ Incorrect
const value = computeHeavy(data);

function MyComponent() {
  const HeavyComponent = require('./HeavyComponent').default;
  return <HeavyComponent />;
}
